[[File:Mordiro.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Cliff jumping as part of a coasteering adventure near [[Porthclais]]]]
[[File:Cliff jumping into guffey cove 2013 crop.jpg|thumb|right|upright|A jump off the cliffs of [[Guffey Gorge (Colorado)|Guffey Gorge]]]]
'''Cliff jumping''' is jumping off a [[cliff]] as a form of sport. When done without equipment, it may be also known as '''tombstoning'''.{{sfn|LaViolette|2012|p=79}} It forms part of the sport of coastal exploration or "[[coasteering]]".{{sfn|LaViolette|2012|p=79}}  When performed with a parachute, it is known as [[BASE jumping]].{{sfn|Williams|Micallef|2009|p=222}} The world record for cliff jumping is currently held by [[Laso Schaller]], with a jump of 58.8&nbsp;m (193&nbsp;ft).<ref name=redbull>{{cite web|last1=Sampiero|first1=Josh|title=This crazy guy set a new cliff-jump world record|url=http://www.redbull.com/en/adventure/stories/1331731012784/highdive-world-record|publisher=[[Red Bull GmbH]]|date=18 August 2015|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>

